      "content": "The regulators aren't really looking for a \"review\" or \"re-weighting.\" They've specifically flagged that any state beyond the original base weights is considered an unverified risk. They want a clean slate to ensure there's zero chance of undocumented behavioral drift. It's a standard safety protocol. Why do you think a re-weighting would be better than just starting from the verified baseline?",
